*INV:	now what we would like you to try to do is to write a letter to anybody in the whole wide world .
%mor:	adv|now pron|what-Int-S1 pron|we-Prs-Nom-P1 aux|would-Fin-S verb|like-Inf-S pron|you-Prs-Acc-S2 part|to verb|try-Inf-S part|to verb|do-Inf-S aux|be-Fin-Ind-Pres-S3 part|to verb|write-Inf-S det|a-Ind-Art noun|letter-Acc adp|to pron|anybody-Ind-S1 adp|in det|the-Def-Art adj|whole-S1 adj|wide-S1 noun|world .
%gra:	1|13|ADVMOD 2|13|NSUBJ-OUTER 3|5|NSUBJ 4|5|AUX 5|2|ACL-RELCL 6|5|OBJ 7|8|MARK 8|5|XCOMP 9|10|MARK 10|8|XCOMP 11|13|COP 12|13|MARK 13|0|ROOT 14|15|DET 15|13|OBJ 16|17|CASE 17|13|OBL 18|22|CASE 19|22|DET 20|22|AMOD 21|22|AMOD 22|17|NMOD 23|13|PUNCT
@Comment:	To Brittany , I want to go back to Arizona again! I Liked it a lot out ther! Love , Chi (first name)
@Comment:	Context notes say Chi lies on floor and kicks feet about as she writes (a girl after my own heart). Chi is left- handed. The letter is to a friend who I think is at Chi's school but Chi writes about going back to Arizona , where Chi and Mot had visited recently. The idea that EXP will keep the letter is very strong , and Mot mentions that they can write a real letter after the visit is over. Chi mouths words to herself to spell them , and she does a pretty good job. Chi comes up with the content of the letter , and Mot helps with spelling and punctuation.
@Comment:	Time is 3:34
